0AD654FD.Line38.BAE4: Taissa, whatever lies ahead, I will be at your side.

18C158DC.VoiceDir36.789BF: Hard for her to say--hard for her to admit she is scared

272C655D.VoiceDir19.789BF: A retort--she isn't happy Timue interrupted the ritual.

2EB6E672.Line34.9118B: Then that is the path you must walk. Now go. The first step is always the hardest. Just remember: you control how tight the chains are.

3114EE91.VoiceDir9.9118B: Relationship between Taissa and Timue is chilly, so there is tension between them. But deep down, Timue cares about Taissa.

3D21F2F3.Line17.9118B: You wish to rid yourself of a demon? You won’t find an answer from the mouths of these witches, or in that tea you brew.

765E0495.Line28.9118B: So tell me: where is the last place you want to be?

C20B8864.Line9.9118B: Because we all know it won’t work for Taissa.

C88B2D0F.Line36.789BF: With Andariel… where it all began…

D6F63990.Line19.789BF: I already know that. I tried -- it didn’t work.

DC698B13.Line26.9118B: Of course not. It can help an old man heal from the loss of a child, yes, but you are plagued by more than just grief. You must face your fears.

E6EF956A.Line40.789BF: Then… perhaps I have a chance to see it through. Meet me at my tower. I will prepare everything.
